com.cisco.mscviewer.tree

Class AVLTreeNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cisco.mscviewer.tree.AVLTreeNode
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    IntervalTreeNode

    public class AVLTreeNode
extends java.lang.Object
    This class implements an Interval Tree (actually, an Augmented Tree). The implementation is slightly tweaked towards its use for storing interactions: the binary tree sorting criteria is the end of the interval, because in our model events can have multiple outgoing interaction but only one incoming one. This allows us to use a single IntervalInfo to store interval in nodes instead of an array.
